Scope:

variable scope --> where the variable can be available to be utilized

global scope: global variables . all functions can use it 

internal scope .. only inside a function


globalvar="checking"
def hours(no_of_days,unit):
  print(f"{no_of_days} days has {no_of_days*24} {unit}")

hours(40,"hours")

def scope_check():
  print(no_of_days)
  print(globalvar)

scope_check()

-->40 days has 960 hours
no_of_days not defined


Another internal variable:

globalvar="checking"

def scope_check():
  int_var="voila"
  print(globalvar)
  print(int_var)
scope_check()

int_var cant be used outside the function

